\section{What is the relationship between a guest operating system and a host operating system in a system like VMware? What factors need to be considered in choosing the host operating system?}

\begin{itemize}
  \item The guest operating system is actually installed within a virtual machine like VMware. To put that into perspective, when you run a virtual machine on your mac OS you can run a different OS like Windows or Linux as guests. The host operating system is installed on the physical hardware and provides the resources, such as CPU/Memory/Storage, for the virtual machine to operate 

  Factors:
    \begin{itemize}
        \item Performance
        \item Security
        \item Compatibility
        \item Support on various topics
    \end{itemize}
 
\end{itemize}


